sections.heading: Definitions
sections.text: 273.01 Definitions.—The following words as used in this act have the meanings set forth in the below subsections, unless a different meaning is required by the context.

sections.heading: Record and inventory of certain property.
Disposition of state-owned tangible personal property.
Penalty
sections.text: 273.09 Penalty.—Any custodian who violates any provision of this chapter or any rule prescribed pursuant to its authority shall be guilty of a misdemeanor of the second degree, punishable as provided in s. 775.082 or s. 775.083.

sections.heading: Repeal
sections.text: 273.10 Repeal.—This act shall not repeal existing law relating to property but shall be interpreted to be supplementary in nature and shall be applicable to the extent that existing law is not in conflict.

sections.heading: Definitions. The following words as used in this act have the meanings set forth in the below subsections, unless a different meaning is required by the context
sections.text: (1)“Custodian” means any elected or appointed state officer, board, commission, or authority, and any other person or agency entitled to lawful custody
